output.dependency: The value in the column representing postal codes (Column 1) could indicate the location of the hospital (Column 2) in that postal area.

The type of care indicated in one column (Column 14) corresponds to a specific measure or category of care reported in another column (Column 15). For example, different surgical infection prevention measures correspond to specific codes.
The numerical code in one column (Column 15) is associated with a detailed description of the care quality measure listed in another column (Column 16).
The type of healthcare facility indicated in one column (Column 11) usually corresponds to the specific classification of the facility in another column (Column 12).
